# ApeironCode environment variables — example template.
#
# Copy this file to .env.local (or export the variables in your shell) and fill
# in only the providers you actually use. NEVER commit real keys: .env and
# .env.local are gitignored, and ApeironCode never prints full keys in setup,
# status, or doctor output.
#
# ApeironCode uses a bring-your-own-key model for cloud providers. Keys are read
# from the environment; no key is required for the local Ollama or mock paths.

# --- Cloud providers (set only what you use) ---
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# GitHub Models (free GitHub-hosted inference) and the GitHub connector.
# Needs "Models: Read" permission for GitHub Models. Never share this token.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# --- Local models (no key needed) ---
# Ollama runs locally; configure with `apeironcode setup --local`.
# Default endpoint:
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434

# --- Mock provider (no key needed) ---
# For offline testing/CI only: `apeironcode setup --provider mock`.
